<section id="about">
  <h2>What I Do</h2>
  <p>
    I'm a Senior AI Engineer and cognitive AI advisor. In my day-to-day I build
    AI-powered products at scale — including tools used by hundreds of thousands
    of users. Through my consultancy, I work with knowledge teams to redesign
    how they use AI and tech in general: identifying where it helps, where it
    quietly harms, and how to build workflows that protect human judgment,
    focus, and skill over time.
  </p>

  <h2>My Why</h2>
  <p>
    I believe technology should be at the service of a more human life. AI,
    blockchain, and emerging systems only create value when they are used with
    intention. My work focuses on quiet technology with real impact —systems
    that respect human attention, free focus and creative energy, and support a
    more intentional way of working and living. I strongly believe that
    technology should reduce cognitive load instead of increasing it, creating
    space for creativity, clarity, and wellbeing. <b
      >Tech is not the goal—people are.</b
    > When used consciously, technology becomes a tool that frees energy instead of
    consuming it.
  </p>

  <h2>What I Love</h2>
  <p>
    Outside work you'll find me learning nerdy things, moving my body, spending
    time in nature, doing manual crafts, traveling, or making homemade desserts.
    I love connecting with curious minds who care about technology and making
    things that actually matter — whether that's to collaborate, exchange ideas,
    or just have a good conversation.
  </p>

  <div class="signature">
    <p>— Sara</p>
  </div>
</section>

